{
  "function_path": "pkg/kubelet/eviction/eviction_manager.go",
  "function_name": "synchronize",
  "justification": "This is a method on the eviction manager (*managerImpl) that performs a single synchronization cycle evaluating resource usage against thresholds. It takes a context, diskInfoProvider to check filesystem info, and podFunc to get active workloads. It returns a slice of evicted pods (at most one) and an error. The function follows the exact procedure described: (1) refreshes memory threshold notifiers from the latest statistics summary (lines 301-308), (2) computes signal observations and determines which thresholds are met, both ignoring and respecting grace periods (lines 311-322), (3) tracks when each threshold was first observed and when each node condition was last observed with a transition period (lines 327-352), (4) filters thresholds to those whose grace periods are met and whose stats have been updated since the last sync (lines 345-360), (5) checks for local storage eviction violations first and returns early if pods are evicted (lines 364-368), (6) sorts remaining thresholds by eviction priority and attempts node-level reclamation like garbage collection (lines 376-390), (7) if node-level reclamation is insufficient, ranks all active pods using a signal-specific ranking function and iterates through ranked pods to evict the first killable pod (lines 395-442). The function updates internal state including met thresholds, node condition timestamps, and observation history (lines 349-360)."
}

